examples.en: Tears choked him.
She choked her anger.
He choked on a piece of bread.
The dust choked and blinded him.
'No!' she choked out.
He choked down his anger.
He was choked with the thought.
Her voice was choked with rage.
The chimney is choked up with soot.
The well was choked (up) with leaves.
Blown clouds of dust choked the riders.
I was too choked with emotion to speak.
Rows and rows of tables choked the room.
Six people choked to death on the fumes.
The room was choked (up) with furniture.
His heart hammered as he choked out the words.
The man took the Emir by the throat and choked him.
He choked at his own spirit's seethe. (H. Trench, 1901)
He hated the meal but choked it down out of politeness.
The stream is choked with its compact incumbency of snow.
He felt his choler rising and choked back an angry reply.
All the choked up hatred he had for Luke suddenly spewed out.
The cartridge is choked tightly into the groove of the socket.
He began to tell about his adventures all over again, but I choked him off.
The team should have won hands down but choked, disappointing the coach and the audience.
